# TransferIntel: Engineering Backlog

> **Delivery status, 20 July 2026.** TI-001, TI-002, TI-003, TI-010, TI-011,
> TI-012, TI-013 and TI-020 are implemented, tested and merged on
> `feat/backlog-00-24`. TI-021 through TI-024 remain open; TI-025 onward were
> always out of scope for this pass. Two tickets were rediagnosed during
> implementation and the corrected causes are recorded inline below. See
> `docs/DELIVERY.md` for what changed, what was rejected, and why.

Prepared 20 July 2026. Target: Premier League summer window closes 1 September 2026.
Site: https://peterdsouza247.github.io/transfer-intel/
Stack assumptions: Python content pipeline generating a static site, deployed to GitHub Pages. Where a ticket assumes something about the codebase it is flagged as an assumption for the engineer to verify.

## How to read this document

Every ticket has: a problem statement, implementation notes, named free services where third parties are needed, and acceptance criteria. Acceptance criteria are the contract. A ticket is not done until every criterion passes.

Priorities:

- **P0**: blocks credibility of the product or breaks the page. Ship before anything else.
- **P1**: revenue and audience infrastructure. Every day of delay during an open window is permanently lost signups.
- **P2**: differentiating features. Build in listed order.
- **P3**: deferred to the January 2027 window or later.

Global constraint: the site is static and hosted on GitHub Pages. No server-side runtime is available. Anything dynamic must be either build-time generated, a third party embed, or a client-side call to an external API.

---

# P0: Bugs

## TI-001: Deals are being falsely promoted to Completed with credibility 100

**Status: DONE.** Root cause confirmed as stated. Fixed structurally with a new `confirmed` status, mandatory completion markers, and a consistency gate. Backfill demoted 7 records, including all six named below.

**Priority:** P0, highest. This is the single most damaging defect on the site.

**Problem.** Multiple deals display status `Completed` and credibility `100 / 100` while their own summary text contradicts that status. Confirmed examples on the live homepage as of 19 July 2026:

| Player | Displayed status | Summary text says |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Leandro Trossard (Arsenal to Beşiktaş) | Completed, 100 | "Fee agreed (£17-20m reported); personal terms being discussed" |
| Luka Vusković (Tottenham to Brighton) | Completed, 100 | "announcement imminent" |
| Álvaro Rodríguez (Elche to Bournemouth) | Completed, 100 | "'Deal agreed' a week ago, then silence. No collapse reported either." |
| Andrey Santos (Chelsea to Man Utd) | Completed, 100 | "all done bar the unveiling" |
| Youri Tielemans (Aston Villa to Man Utd) | Completed, 100 | "Announcement expected this week" |
| Johan Manzambi (Freiburg to Aston Villa) | Completed, 100 | "Villa hijacked Newcastle's agreed deal" |

All six carry the marker "Confirmed (auto-updated 2026-07-16)" or a similar auto-update stamp, which points at a single defect in the pipeline rather than six separate data entry errors.

**Root cause hypothesis.** The auto-update pass appears to treat any deal it re-encounters in the feed, or any deal that has not been reported as collapsed, as confirmation, and writes `status = completed` and `credibility = 100`. Absence of contradicting news is being read as positive confirmation.

**Why it matters.** The site's entire value proposition is that it distinguishes real deals from noise. A visitor who knows Trossard has not signed for Beşiktaş will not trust any other number on the page. This defect is more costly than every missing feature in this document combined.

**Implementation.**

1. Locate the auto-update stage in the pipeline. Assumption: a function that reruns over existing deal records with fresh feed items.
2. Remove any code path that can set `status = completed` without an explicit completion signal.
3. Define an explicit completion signal set. A deal may only be promoted to `Completed` when the source text contains a confirmed-signing marker. Suggested marker list, to be tuned:
   - "here we go" from Romano specifically
   - "has signed", "completes move", "officially joined", "unveiled", "announced"
   - Presence of the club's own domain in the source URL, which is the strongest possible signal
4. Introduce a distinct status `Confirmed pending announcement` for the genuine case where a Tier 1 source reports a completed medical and all terms agreed but no official announcement exists. Cap credibility for this status at 90, not 100. Reserve 100 exclusively for club-announced deals.
5. Add a hard consistency gate that runs after every build and fails the build on violation:
   - `status == completed` requires `source_tier == 1` AND a completion marker recorded on the record AND a non-null `completed_date`
   - `credibility == 100` requires `status == completed`
   - `status == completed` requires the deal is not also present in the collapsed set
6. Add a `last_verified_at` timestamp to every record, distinct from `updated_at`. `updated_at` changes when the pipeline touches the record. `last_verified_at` changes only when a source actually reasserts the deal.
7. Backfill: manually audit all 31 records currently marked Completed. Demote every one that lacks an official club announcement. Expect roughly 6 to 10 demotions.

**Acceptance criteria.**

- No record on the site displays `Completed` without a recorded completion marker and a source tier of 1.
- No record displays credibility 100 unless its status is `Completed`.
- A new status value `Confirmed pending announcement` renders correctly in the Window Pulse counters, the credibility index list, and the deal detail pages.
- The consistency gate runs in CI and fails the build on any violation. Deliberately corrupt one record in a test fixture and confirm the build fails.
- The six deals listed in the table above display statuses consistent with their summary text.
- Re-running the pipeline twice over an unchanged feed produces zero status changes on the second run. This is the regression test for the whole class of bug.

